headlines.description: — Jimmy Butler scored 23 points, Bam Adebayo added 18 points and 11 rebounds and the Miami Heat showed their experience down the stretch in a 100-97 win over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jimmy Butler scores 23 as Heat hold off Cavaliers 100-97

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — LeBron James will soon be the NBA's top scorer, though that was never his focus.
headlines.shortLinkText: James has triple-double, leads Lakers past Knicks in OT

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard scored 33 points and Norman Powell added 27 to help the Los Angeles Clippers beat the Chicago Bulls 108-103 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Leonard, Powell lead Clippers past Bulls, 108-103

headlines.description: — Khris Middleton is making the most of his limited minutes as he works his way back from injuries that kept him from playing for much of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks beat Hornets 124-115 for 5th consecutive victory

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray is locked in right now — with his shot, with his swagger and especially with his confidence in his team.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray, Jokic help Nuggets hold off Pelicans 122-113
